    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello everyone,\n\nI’m not sure if this is a possible bug or a misconfiguration on my side, but I’m experiencing issues when using Neovim built from source.\nIt seems to behave differently depending on the directory from which I launch it. When I start Neovim from within my configuration directory (~/.config/nvim), everything works fine and no errors appear.\nHowever, when I start Neovim from any other directory, I consistently get the following error message:\n```\nError in /home/michelangelo/.config/nvim/init.lua:\nE5113: Lua chunk: /home/michelangelo/.config/nvim/init.lua:1: module 'core.pack' not found:\n        no field package.preload['core.pack']\n        no file './core/pack.lua'\n        no file '/home/michelangelo/neovim/.deps/usr/share/luajit-2.1/core/pack.lua'\n        no file '/usr/local/share/lua/5.1/core/pack.lua'\n        no file '/usr/local/share/lua/5.1/core/pack/init.lua'\n        no file '/home/michelangelo/neovim/.deps/usr/share/lua/5.1/core/pack.lua'\n        no file '/home/michelangelo/neovim/.deps/usr/share/lua/5.1/core/pack/init.lua'\n        no file './core/pack.so'\n        no file '/usr/local/lib/lua/5.1/core/pack.so'\n        no file '/home/michelangelo/neovim/.deps/usr/lib/lua/5.1/core/pack.so'\n        no file '/usr/local/lib/lua/5.1/loadall.so'\n        no file './core.so'\n        no file '/usr/local/lib/lua/5.1/core.so'\n        no file '/home/michelangelo/neovim/.deps/usr/lib/lua/5.1/core.so'\n        no file '/usr/local/lib/lua/5.1/loadall.so'\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'require'\n        /home/michelangelo/.config/nvim/init.lua:1: in main chunk\n```\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI've builded neovim from source using the following commands:\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/neovim/neovim\ncd neovim\nmake CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release\nsudo make install\n```\nAnd when i've tried to reinstall i've also removed the following folders:\n```\nsudo rm -rf /usr/local/share/nvim\nsudo rm -rf /usr/local/lib/nvim\nsudo rm -f /usr/local/bin/nvim\n```\nand sometimes also i've deleted the neovim folder cloned from the repository.\n\nMy neovim settings so far are:\n\n```\n-- init.lua\nrequire(\"core.pack\")\nrequire(\"plugins.lsp\")\n```\nand\n\n```\n-- core/pack.lua\nvim.pack.add({\n  { src = \"https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig\" },\n})\n```\nalso\n\n```\n-- /plugins/lsp.lua\nvim.lsp.config('clangd', {\n  cmd = { 'clangd', '--background-index' },\n  root_markers = { 'compile_commands.json', '.git' },\n})\n\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect that the message error written before is shown every time so not depending on the folder where i launch neovim. In any case the LSP is not working.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-696+g76cacf6f8b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot tested\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n7.0.10-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNU bash, version 5.3.9(1)-release \n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
