            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> ~/.config/nvim/core/pack.lua # wrong\n> ~/.config/nvim/lua/core/pack.lua # right\n> \n> -- ~/.config/nvim/init.lua\n> require(\"core.pack\")\n> \n> Then the import should work in other directories too:\n\nthis solved the issue, noob error i'd say! Thanks!",
